                                <locus from="1r" to="12v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Calendar</title>
                                <note>
                                    <p>Notable feasts:</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="2r" to="2r" scheme="folios"/>: St Augulus (7 Feb.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="2r" to="2r" scheme="folios"/>: 79 Martyrs (21 Feb.) Hur rapportera felet? Hs har 89</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="3v" to="3v" scheme="folios"/>: St Marin (<foreign xml:lang="la">Marinus miles</foreign>, 3 Mar.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="3v" to="3v" scheme="folios"/>: St Rupert (27 March; addition);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="6r" to="6r" scheme="folios"/>: St Wilibald (7 July);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="6r" to="6r" scheme="folios"/>: St Henry (13 July);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="8r" to="8r" scheme="folios"/>: St Oswald (5 Aug.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="9r" to="9r" scheme="folios"/>: St Euverte (7 Sep.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="9v" to="9v" scheme="folios"/>: St Sigo (Sequanus, 19 Sep.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="10r" to="10r" scheme="folios"/>: 300 (or 360) Martyrs of Cologne (15 Oct.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="11r" to="11r" scheme="folios"/>: St Serapion (14 Nov.).</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="13r" to="205r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Psalms</title>
                                <note>
                                    <p>Psalms 1-150.</p>
                                    <p>The two bifolia making up <locus from="138" to="138" scheme="folios"/>/ <locus from="141" to="141" scheme="folios"/>and <locus from="139" to="139" scheme="folios"/>/ <locus from="140" to="140" scheme="folios"/> respectively have been placed in the wrong order and should switch places. This appears to have happened already in the middle ages, as a contemporary hand seems to make a note on the incorrect order of the psalms at <locus from="140r" to="140r" scheme="folios"/>(<quote>sequitur dominus regnauit <unclear quantity="16" unit="chars"/>
                                        </quote>). The hand adding the psalm numbers has also erased the <quote>7</quote> in its original <quote>97</quote> and changed this to a <quote>9</quote> - i.e. the Hebrew number for <foreign xml:lang="la">Dominus regnavit</foreign> - erasing in the process part of the medieval note. The note on <locus from="141r" to="141r" scheme="folios"/> seems, however to pertain not to the order of the psalms but to the antiphons (<quote>Cantate domino <supplied reason="damage">canti</supplied>cum nouum Be<supplied reason="damage">atus homo</supplied> quem tu erudier<supplied reason="damage">is</supplied>
                                        </quote>.)</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="205r" to="219v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Canticles</title>
                                <note>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="205r" to="205r" scheme="folios"/>: Canticle of Isaias the Prophet (Isa. 12);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="205v" to="205v" scheme="folios"/>: Canticle of Ezechias (Isa. 38:10-20);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="206v" to="206v" scheme="folios"/>: Canticle of Anna (1 Sam. 2:1-10);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="208r" to="208r" scheme="folios"/>: Canticle of Moses (Exod. 15:1-19);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="209v" to="209v" scheme="folios"/>: Canticle of Habacuc (Hab. 3:2-19);</p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="212r" to="212r" scheme="folios"/>: Canticle of Moses (Deut. 32:1-43);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="216v" to="216v" scheme="folios"/>: Canticle of the Three Children (Dan. 3:57-88);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="217v" to="217v" scheme="folios"/>: Canticle of Zachary / Benedictus (Luke 1:68-79);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="218v" to="218v" scheme="folios"/>: Canticle of the Blessed Virgin Mary / Magnificat (Luke 1:46-55);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="219r" to="219r" scheme="folios"/>: Canticle of Simeon / Nunc dimittis (Luke 2:29-32);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="219v" to="219v" scheme="folios"/>: Te deum.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="221r" to="223v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">The Athanasian Creed</title>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem defective="true">
                                <locus from="223v" to="223v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Litany</title>
                                <note>The litany is incomplete; leaves missing after <locus from="223" to="223" scheme="folios"/>. The following section is written in a different hand (<locus from="224r" to="229r" scheme="folios"/>); before the main hand resumes, on <locus from="229r" to="229r" scheme="folios"/>, some text has been erased.</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="224r" to="229r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Weekly cycle for Lauds</title>
                                <incipit>ETerne rerum conditor</incipit>
                                <explicit>dirigendos pedes nostros in viam pacis deus israhel</explicit>
                                <note>Invitatories, antiphons, psalms, hymns, and verses for the weekly cycle of Lauds; for Monday and Tuesday, also chapter. The hymns are given in full; the other items by incipit only.</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="229r" to="239v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Office for the dead</title>
                                <rubric>Vigilie mortuorum maiores Invitatorium</rubric>
                                <incipit>Circumdederunt me gemitus</incipit>
                                <explicit>Lauda anima mea dominum</explicit>
                            </msItem>
                        </msContents>
