                            <handDesc>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-1">
                                    <locus from="1r" to="223v" scheme="folios"/>Textualis, spacious with few abbreviations and very little biting. <!--biting 17v--></handNote>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-2">
                                    <locus from="224r" to="229r" scheme="folios"/>Textualis. Possibly two hands; note <quote>f</quote> and <quote>s</quote> descending slightly below the line towards the end.</handNote>
                            </handDesc>
                            <additions>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Bottom right corner, in black ink: the monogram <quote>EF (or CF) c</quote>.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="13r" to="203r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Beginning at Ps 1 and continuing until Ps 147, a contemporary hand has added the antiphons, and occasionally also versicles and responsories (e.g. <locus from="26v" to="26v" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="43v" to="43v" scheme="folios"/>), for the psalms in the margin, using rubrics in red and with capitals touched in red. The incipit of the antiphon precedes the psalm or psalms it belongs to and the full antiphon is given at the end of the psalm or sequence of psalms. In several instances, the writing of the first hand has been erased and a second medieval hand has added a different antiphon on top of the erasure, e.g. <locus from="29v" to="29v" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="33v" to="33v" scheme="folios"/>.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="13r" to="204v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Psalm numbers according to the Hebrew numbering in ink in the margin by an early modern hand. Starting at <locus from="23v" to="23v" scheme="folios"/> (Ps 11), Gallican (Vulgate) numbers in pencil below, in parentheses.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="140r" to="140r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>A marginal note in a contemporary hand, presumably on the incorrect order of the psalms:<quote> sequitur dominus regnauit e<unclear quantity="16" unit="chars"/>
                                        </quote>.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="240r" to="240r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>List of responsories and verses for vigils in a cursive hand.</note>
                                </p>
                            </additions>
                            <decoDesc>
                                <p>Main text in dark ink; rubrics in red. The more elaborate decoration scheme of the initials corresponds to the traditional division of the psalms into three groups of 50, Pss 1-50, Pss 51-100, and Pss 101-150. The less elaborate decoration scheme corresponds to the secular cursus, with larger, decorated initials at Ps. 1, 26, 38, 52, 68, 80, 97, 109 (Sunday-Saturday Matins and Sunday Vespers). The exceptions are Pss 52 and 97, which are decorated according to the more elaborate scheme.</p>
                                <decoNote type="initials">
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1r" to="12r" scheme="folios"/>: <quote>KL</quote> over 3 lines in blue and red at head of each month.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="13r" to="13r" scheme="folios"/> (Ps. 1): illuminated opening initial <quote>B</quote> over 9 lines inside a square mauve frame with a black outline; letter body in a vine stem shape in blue, green, and red decorated with a scallop pattern, outlined in black and with foliage in blue, red, and green; counter space in gold leaf.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="80r" to="80r" scheme="folios"/> (Ps. 51), <locus from="141r" to="141r" scheme="folios"/> (Ps. 97), <locus from="143r" to="143r" scheme="folios"/> (Ps. 101): foliate initial over 4-5 lines inside a square black frame with a background in green, or mauve and gold leaf; letter body in a vine stem shape in blue decorated with a scallop pattern, outlined in black and with stems in red, or red and mauve, and foliage in green; counter space in gold leaf.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="80v" to="80v" scheme="folios"/> (Ps. 52): foliate initial over 4 lines inside a black frame with a background in gold leaf; letter body in vine stem shape in blue decorated with a scallop pattern, outlined in black and foliage in green; in the counter space, a red flower with green leaves on a black background.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="43v" to="43v" scheme="folios"/> (Ps. 26), <locus from="63r" to="63r" scheme="folios"/> (Ps 38), <locus from="98r" to="98r" scheme="folios"/> (Ps. 68), <locus from="120r" to="120r" scheme="folios"/> (Ps. 80), <locus from="162r" to="162r" scheme="folios"/> (Ps. 109): puzzle psalm initials over 5 lines in red and blue and counter space filled with penwork in red and blue.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="13v" to="223v" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="229v" to="238v" scheme="folios"/>: plain psalm or item initials over 2 lines alternating in red and blue, ascenders/descenders extending into the margin.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="13r" to="223v" scheme="folios"/>: plain initials over 1 line alternating in red and blue.</p>
                                    <p> For further description of the decoration see <ref target="http://urn.kb.se/resolve?urn=urn:nbn:se:alvin:portal:record-472890">Lindqvist Sandgren</ref>.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                            </decoDesc>
                        </physDesc>
